The paper discusses MIMO processing in wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact on standard specifications, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of rate-splitting as a strategy for improving spectral and energy efficiencies is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
